<img src="https://i1.wp.com/tooxclusive.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Burna-Boy-and-Jorja-Smith-550x367-1.jpg?ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The smash hit “Be Honest” was released in 2019 by British singer, Jorja Smith which featured Burna Boy. The track immediately became a fan favorite and received millions of streams upon its release. The track has now been awarded a platinum certification for selling more 200,000 units in France. In France, according to the National Syndicate of Phonographic Publishing (SNEP), for a track to be certified Platinum, it must have sold 100,000 units.  Burna Boy now joins Wizkid as the only Nigerian artiste to have a song certified platinum or higher in France. as “Bella” by MHD featuring Wizkid earlier this year was certified Platinum in France. France Certifications (@snep): @JorjaSmith Ft. @burnaboy, “Be Honest”, Platinum (200K Units). — chartdata_nigeria (@chartdata_naija) June 4, 2020 ??????? https://t.co/qBsorBvpXY — Burna Boy (@burnaboy) June 4, 2020 The post Jorja Smith & Burna Boy’s Smash Hit “Be Honest” Certified Platinum In France appeared first on tooXclusive. Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.